    {
      "first_name": "Francis Frederick",
      "last_name": "Cleaver",
      "born_year": 1832,
      "died_year": 1900,
      "bio": "Francis Frederick Cleaver was the son of Joseph Cleaver (b.1798) and Sarah Cleaver (b.c.1801). His siblings included Emma (b.c.1828), Alfred/Albert (b.c.1834), Frederick (b.c.1836), and Arthur (b.c.1841). Francis was a lace dresser and bleacher employing 80 people in 1881. He lived at 25 Cavendish Crescent South with his wife Emma and their children. His brother Albert Cleaver was also prominent in the Nottingham lace industry and married Mary Adelaide Allen (daughter of Richard Allen).",
